Before you build the Motion2D library and example programs, you must run the
"configure" script to set the platform information and other build
settings.  You can use the -platform option to specify the operating
system and compiler you are using.

Supported platforms and compilers:

  linux-g++	    
  sunos-g++
  solaris-g++	    solaris-CC
  irix64-g++	    irix64-CC
  cygwin-g++
  Visual-C++

Limitations:

  Use Gnu Make (gmake) to compile Motion2D.

Example:

  ./configure -help
  ./configure -platform linux-g++ -verbose

Customization:

  You can create your own custom configuration by adding new files to
  the configs directory. 

